CSS `::marker` allows customizing bullet content, but it has a limited set of properties it supports. It’s more semantically robust, though. Example:

```css
.hero-bullets { list-style: none; }
.hero-bullets li::marker { content: "✓ "; font-weight: 900; color: var(--accent-600); }
```

Not all properties apply, and cross-browser support is good (Chrome, Firefox, Safari). Instead of hex, use color tokens like `var(--accent-green)` or `currentColor`. For alignment fix, a different approach might work.

